2026-03-20 v1.0.2 optimization log

Scope:
- Reduce AGET/ASET JSON decode/encode overhead.
- Separate index flush modes: strong sync vs async flush.
- Add key lock wait observability.

Changes:
1) Batch index flush pipeline
- Added batch append APIs for key/search/idempotency indexes.
- Reworked BatchSet to apply events in-memory first, then flush indexes in batch.
- Reduced per-event open/write/sync amplification.

2) Configurable index flush mode
- Added performance.index_flush_mode with values: sync | async.
- Default remains sync.
- Added async index flush worker with queue + sync fallback when queue is full.

3) Lock wait metrics
- Added wait-time sampling for lockKey/rlockKey/lockKeys/rlockKeys.
- Metrics now include key_lock_wait_count/p50/p95.

4) DSL hot path optimization
- Added fast parsing path for common scalar ASET items.
- Optimized AGET key splitting to reduce string allocation overhead.

Validation:
- go test ./... passed after optimization changes.
- RW stress throughput improved significantly compared with pre-batch-flush baseline.

Notes:
- Transfer hotspot bottleneck still exists for single main-account key contention.
- Next phase should prioritize account sharding and further async persistence tuning.
